snippet.textDisplay:
Firstly, Lauren Michelle Speed and Cameron Reid Hamilton congratulations on your union and thank you for the real life beautiful fairytale you both revived around the world.

This is beyond both of you, much more than you can ever imagine.

I think both of you should gift to yourselves, generations to come and the world at large, one person singing to the other, duets, ballads, medleys, music videos, your own renditions of short or long movies. e.g your own movie and animation and Cinderella.

Songs I envisioned for both of you are based on your story so far:

Run to you by Whitney Houston.
Endless love by Lionel Richie and Dianna Ross.
Spinderella by Big Daddy Kane and Spinderella.
Having my baby by Paul Anker.
Head to toe by Lisa Lisa & Cult Jam.
The wonder of you by Elvis Presley.
Can I touch you there by Michael Bolton.
Ain't too proud to beg Salt N Pepa.

Don't worry about whether or not you are great singers or actors. It is more about the power, authenticity, chemistry, love and vulnerability of your union..

If you have to lip sync or mime, that will be fine.

The only catch is, the presentation and delivery standard has to be world class because that is where you both belong.

I'm sure it's going to be better than some of the very best we have currently.

All the best.
